Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 1:23 PM - case called.  Defendant Yamonie S Williams not in court.  Attorney Andrew R Polzin in court for State of Wisconsin.  Defendant fails to appear - bonded out of custody.  Statement by Atty Polzin - requests the cash bond be forfeited and a warrant issued.  State did not receive a Governor's Warrant.  Discussions regarding statue.  Court orders the cash bond be forfeited and further orders the immediately arrest without a warrant; outstanding warrant in Iowa.

records.descr: Application for specific judicial assign approved

records.addlTxt: Extradition hearing on August 11, 2022 at 01:15 pm.

9:03 AM Prosecuting attorney Andrew R Polzin in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Yamonie S Williams in court, in custody without counsel. (Extradition from Iowa) Statements by Polzin. Defendant has not been able to obtain counsel. No Governors warrant received as of this time. Asking detainer remain. Court questions defendant. Ms. Williams tried to contact the PD office three times but was not able to contact an attorney.  Court contacts public defenders office.  Public defenders office will send an attorney to the jail to speak to her today.  This will end up getting transferred to Branch II.  Court will calculate out 30 days.  August 9th would be day 30.  Attempted to get a date for hearing.  Will have to be scheduled off the record.
Extradition hearing on July 22, 2022 at 09:00 am.

2:15 PM Prosecuting attorney Andrew R Polzin in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Yamonie S Williams appeared by video, in custody. Case called appearances given.  Not a victim rights case.  This is for extradition to IOWA.   Court questions the deft if she is going to waive or fight the extradition.  No govern warrant as of yet. Court going to commit the deft to LISO for 30 days.
Extradition hearing scheduled for July 22, 2022 at 09:00 am.
